&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;For business leaders who want to get AI right, Gladly is the only customer experience AI that delivers the cost savings they need AND the customer devotion that drives lasting business value. With over a decade of singular CX focus and trusted by the world&#39;s most customer-centric brands including Crate &amp;amp; Barrel, Breeze Airways, and Ulta Beauty, Gladly was designed for devotion, not deflection: purpose-built to engage customers and turn every conversation into lasting relationship equity. The result is experiences that are radically personal and effortlessly scalable, emotionally intelligent and operationally efficient.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;At the heart of our simply powerful platform, Gladly maintains one continuous conversation across all channels while striking the perfect balance of AI and human connection. With 450M+ conversations powered globally, $510M+ cumulative cost savings delivered for customers, and a 65% increase in CSAT, this is a team where your work has real impact at scale. Learn more at&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gladly.ai&quot;&gt; www.gladly.ai&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll join Gladly&#39;s Marketing team, reporting to our Senior Manager of Demand Generation. It&#39;s a small, fast-moving team that runs on autonomy and initiative: we give people real ownership of their work and trust them to run with it rather than wait for direction. We favor momentum over process, welcome bold ideas, and treat candid feedback as part of how we get better together. Because the website supports nearly every part of the business, you&#39;ll partner broadly across teams to bring their work to life on the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gladly is looking for a Web Experience Manager to own how our website gets built, maintained, and continuously improved. You&#39;ll be the hands-on expert for our site, guiding pages from concept through launch, shaping layout and design decisions, and using data to steadily improve how the site performs and converts. This is a role with real, ongoing ownership of our web presence. You are equal parts builder and optimizer. You can build and maintain pages, keep Core Web Vitals strong, and QA a release across devices, and you can just as readily find where the site is losing visitors, run a rigorous A/B test, and prove the impact in GA4. You bring ideas and solutions, not just execution, and you welcome feedback on a highly visible, public site. You&#39;ll own our web build end to end, with real creative latitude and a growth path as an individual contributor that doesn&#39;t require moving into people management. We&#39;re looking for someone with the initiative to thrive in a fast-paced, autonomous environment and the craft to make our site both beautiful and high-converting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Site Build&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, launch, and maintain landing pages and templates in Sanity, and keep our CMS and component library in good working order.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide page layout and design decisions, translating brand direction into pages that look right and perform well, without managing the design team itself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;QA every release before it ships, catching visual, functional, and cross-device issues early. Own Core Web Vitals, site speed, and SEO fundamentals like schema markup and indexing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
